{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92a04073-e25e-4b9e-897b-34bac3ea6110","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll answer based on general .NET knowledge:\n\n**Template:** Use `webapi` — create with:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No auth (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n```bash\n# Azure AD single org\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d024128-b4a7-487b-b24c-6012c6ab1135","outputTokens":264,"requestId":"CFCF:274C4A:10FCA98:1341077:69F93E2A"},"id":"727308d4-24ac-407f-b20a-a5c63366fd46","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:47.750Z","parentId":"719e3a11-aa92-494c-80c3-06e8fc2136a5"}
